right if you use this path:

```json
"default_config": {
    "fee_recipient": "0x8943545177806ED17B9F23F0a21ee5948eCaa776",
    "gas_limit": "90000000",
    "graffiti": "prysm",
    "builder": {
      "enabled": true,
      "builders": [
        {"url": "http://buildoor-lodestar-nethermind-2-1:8080"},
        {"url": "http://buildoor-lodestar-nethermind-2-2:8080"}
      ],
      "proxy": "http://side-car:9001",
      "max_execution_payment": "18446744073709551615"
    }
  }
```

all the muxing can be defined at the proxy layer. but the builder list still must live in the VC config or else the proxy will never receive valid signed auths. (if the VC fetched the config details from somewhere else then the builder list could live at the proxy)
